author: CNN
description: President Trump showed reporters renderings of the new ballroom inside the Oval Office, which show how the construction would take place where the East Wing once stood. He defended his plans to build the space — which he said will cost “about $300 million.”
title: Trump explains demolition of East Wing

author: CNN
description: Maine Senate candidate Graham Platner revealed he covered up a tattoo resembling a Nazi symbol, saying it came from a drunken night 18 years ago while serving in the Marines. Despite the controversy, Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-VT) is standing by his endorsement.    #CNN #News
title: Democratic Senate candidate says he covered up tattoo once linked to Nazi symbol

author: CNN
description: Demolition of the White House East Wing began Monday as President Donald Trump adds a $200 million, 90,000-square-foot ballroom. CNN observed an excavator tearing down portions of the East Wing.
title: East Wing facade barely recognizable as demolition continues

author: CNN
description: CNN found hundreds of US military flights in the Caribbean carried out by intelligence-gathering planes and tankers used to refuel jets in midair, as tensions between the US and Venezuela simmer. CNN’s Natasha Bertrand reports. #cnn #news #shorts
title: Making sense of US military flights off the coast of Venezuela

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump said he had “canceled” an anticipated meeting with Russian President Vladimir Putin, telling reporters at the White House, “It just didn’t feel right to me.” “It didn’t feel like we were going to get to the place we have to get – so I canceled it, but we’ll do it in the future,” Trump told reporters gathered in the Oval Office. #CNN #News
title: Trump cancels meeting with Putin, announces new sanctions on Russian oil companies

author: CNN
description:
Construction crews began demolishing part of the White House East Wing for President Trump’s $200 million, 90,000-square-foot ballroom—funded privately but built during a federal shutdown.
#cnn   #News
title: Excavators tear Into WH East Wing for Trump’s $200M ballroom project

author: CNN
description: Senate Democrats made clear today that they believe it is on Republicans, including President Donald Trump, to change strategy and negotiate with them, as they continue to push to extend enhanced Affordable Care Act subsidies to reopen the government. It is unclear when the Senate will vote next on the GOP funding bill, which has repeatedly failed. #CNN #News
title: Government shutdown reaches 22 days, the second-longest on record

author: CNN
description: At the fall owners meeting, NFL commissioner Roger Goodell was asked if the league stands by its decision to have musician Bad Bunny headline the Super Bowl LX halftime show.
title: NFL commissioner asked about any change to Bad Bunny at Super Bowl

author: CNN
description: Shots were heard outside Serbia’s parliament building and a fire also broke out among tents that are currently built up nearby. According to officials, one man was seriously wounded. An investigation into the incident is ongoing.
title: Shots heard outside Serbia’s parliament building

author: CNN
description: The remains of the hilltop mansion from “Succession” have been labeled as a public nuisance by the Los Angeles City Council, along with seven other properties. The house burned down in the Palisades fire in January, and owners have reportedly missed the deadline to clear up the hazardous waste left behind.
title: Mansion from hit show ‘Succession’ labeled a public nuisance

author: CNN
description: CNN's Jake Tapper used OpenAI's new Sora 2 app, an AI video generator, to highlight some of the risks of AI video.
title: Jake Tapper creates AI videos to highlight the risks

author: CNN
description: Illinois state Rep. Hoan Huynh (D) says he was stopped by Immigration and Customs Enforcement agents at gunpoint while he was patrolling the community on Tuesday. The Democratic lawmaker shared a video of the incident to X where he can be seen in the passenger seat as agents approach the driver’s window. Huynh joins CNN’s Brianna Keilar to discuss the incident.  #CNN #News
title: Illinois lawmaker says federal agents stopped his vehicle at gunpoint

author: CNN
description: A country western bar in the middle of Seoul? Welcome to Grand Ole Opry, the city's legendary honky-tonk where cowboy boots find their home in South Korea, led by the one and only Mama Kim. #cnn #news #travel
title: A fortune teller told this woman to open a bar, and 50 years later it's still open

title: Russia launches large-scale air attack on Ukraine

author: CNN
description: 'I think she would be very proud and it's a victory for her even after her passing': Amy Wallace, co-author of "Nobody's Girl" details what it was like to work with Epstein survivor Virginia Roberts Giuffre's to write her memoir.  #CNN #News
title: Co-author of Epstein survivor Virginia Giuffre's memoir details new revelations from the book

title: ‘It really does damage’: Business owner on the shutdown’s impact on his employees

title: A first look at Samsung’s Galaxy XR headset

author: CNN
description: Russia launched a large-scale air attack on Ukraine early Wednesday, causing power outages across most of the country, setting homes ablaze and killing at least six people, including a six-month-old baby, Ukrainian authorities said. The attack, which involved drones, missiles and fighter jets, targeted vast swathes of the country, including the capital Kyiv, and came as uncertainty swirled over a proposed Putin-Trump summit. CNN’s Nic Robertson and Kevin Liptak report.  #CNN #News
title: Trump says meeting with Putin could be waste of time as Russia steps up attacks in Ukraine

author: CNN
description: Paul Ingrassia is no longer the nominee to lead the Office of Special Counsel, two White House officials told CNN on Tuesday, after his chances of getting through the Senate confirmation imploded following reports of racist text messages that he allegedly sent to a group chat.  #CNN #News
title: Trump nominee drops out after KFILE report, more vile statements surface

author: CNN
description: CNN senior legal analyst Elie Honig breaks down the chances that President Donald Trump could receive $230 million in compensation from the Department of Justice for its past investigations into him.  #CNN #News
title: Elie Honig predicts the likelihood Trump can get $230 million in compensation from DOJ

author: CNN
description: A new report in The Atlantic found nearly a third of ICE recruits failing fitness tests, and many failing the civics test requirements. CNN Senior Political Commentator Scott Jennings says this report is a good thing and shows how ICE is weeding out unqualified agents. CNN Senior Political Commentator Ana Navarro disagrees and the NewsNight panel weighs in. #CNN #News
title: ‘The system is working!’: Scott Jennings, Ana Navarro clash over ICE recruits failing tests

author: CNN
description: Virginia Giuffre’s sister-in-law spoke with CNN’s Kaitlan Collins about Giuffre’s fear that she might die a sex slave. #cnn #virginiagiuffre
title: Virginia Giuffre's sister-in-law reacts to memoir

author: CNN
description: Peru’s President Jose Jeri declared a 30-day state of emergency in the capital Lima and the neighboring province of Callao, saying the move was to battle rising crime. #cnn #news #peru
title: Peru declares state of emergency in the capital

author: CNN
description: More than 500 people took to the streets in Dublin after a man was arrested for attacking a young girl, according to The Irish Times. Protesters set a police van on fire and attacked officers outside a building housing asylum seekers. #cnn #dublin
title: Anti-immigrant protesters set police van on fire

author: CNN
description: Lee Vogler, council member of Danville, Virginia, has been released from the hospital after being doused in gasoline and set on fire outside his place of employment in July. #cnn #news
title: City official returns to work after set on fire

author: CNN
description: A New York man who was convicted of charges related to the January 6, 2021, Capitol attack was arrested Sunday on a charge that he threatened to kill Democratic House Minority Leader Hakeem Jeffries. According to New York State Police, an anonymous source told the FBI that the man, Christopher Moynihan, had said on Friday that “in a few days, he would kill Congressman Jeffries in New York City for ‘the future,’” court records say. #CNN #News
title: Pardoned Capitol rioter charged with attempting to kill Hakeem Jeffries

author: CNN
description: A chaotic scene briefly erupted in downtown Manhattan when ICE agents began arresting illegal street vendors, a law enforcement official told CNN. It was not immediately clear how many arrests were made. #cnn, #news
title: ICE raids street vendors in NYC

author: CNN
description: Several GOP lawmakers have suggested that President Donald Trump take a more direct role in resolving the shutdown in recent days, including potentially opening up negotiations with Democrats if it’s what’s required to end the standoff. “If he gets involved, he can move it,” GOP Sen. Tommy Tuberville said of Trump. “He can make a decision on what we do.” #CNN #News
title: Shutdown: Trump would 'love to meet' Democrats, but 'we want the country open first'

author: CNN
description: CNN's Kaitlan Collins asks President Donald Trump about a New York Times report that he is seeking $230 million from his own Department of Justice to settle past complaints involving the Russia investigation and the classified documents investigation.
title: Collins asks Trump about report that he’s seeking $230M from his own DOJ

author: CNN
description: CNN Chief White House Correspondent Kaitlan Collins asks President Trump if he would meet with New York City mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani if he were to be elected.
title: Trump says he'll speak to Zohran Mamdani if he wins NYC mayoral race
